# Concurrent post PRs each append one row to growth/image-concepts.md (the hero
# concept ledger). Without help, two branches appending at the file tail collide
# on every merge. The built-in `union` merge driver resolves this by KEEPING
# BOTH SIDES' lines instead of conflicting — exactly right for an append-only
# ledger with unique per-slug rows. GitHub honors this driver on PR merges, so
# the recurring ledger conflict disappears at the source.
growth/image-concepts.md merge=union
